Lecture : 7
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Q - When useEffect is called?
  If no dependency array => useEffect is called  on every render
  If the  dependency array is empty [] => useEffect is called  on initial render(just once)
  If the  dependency array is not empty => called evertimes btnName is changed

→ never use useState outside of the Component. It is used to create local state variables inside the functional component
→ Never create useState variable inside the (if-else, forloops or function) conditions. It creates inconsistency. Always create inside the functional component at the top level.


